@Kane610 @tinloaf so i am ok of having both (both events and entities) but i don't see much usage for an entity for a ZHASwitch which only responds with some code like 1001 or 2001 or whatever code it comes back with because that depends on the manufacturer. That is only what ZHASwitches does send some codes. The codes doesn't really matter for HASS but for the user they do because 1001 could mean he clicked button up and 1002 could be button down. This information i don't see useful in the history, in the recorder maybe.

For me as a user i think that if you make an entity for a switch i shouldn't spend time to write a template sensor for each switch to get the battery out from the attribute because that's what i want, a list of all sensors battery. There should be sensors for battery for each sensor just like @Kane610 has implemented. IMO

It's obvious that cleanest approach is to create entities for all sensors where some sensors will have more entities than one e.g a battery sesnors, this is inline with other components in HASS. Also as an additional bonus add events for sensors would be great IMO. In this way user doesn't need to choose between events or entities, he get's both.

